{"lemma":"حَبَّ","slug":"حَبَّ","root":"ح.ب.ب","root_slug":"ح-ب-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ب-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَبّ","root":"حبب","pos":"N","occurrence_count":7},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":7,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":17},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n6839"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to love, to like","tags":["rare"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to give focus, to give attention","tags":["rare"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be loved","tags":["rare"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to love","tags":["rare"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be loved","tags":["rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَبَّ (ḥabba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"love","tags":["rare"],"examples":[{"text":"وَتُحِبُّونَ الْمَالَ حُبًّا جَمًّا","english":"And you love wealth with abounding love."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"affection, attachment","tags":["rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"beloved, darling","tags":["rare"],"examples":[{"text":"وَمَا كُلُّ مَنْ يَهْوَى يَعِفُّ إِذَا خَلَا / عَفَافِي وَيُرْضِي ٱلْحِبَّ وَٱلْخَيْلُ تَلْتَقِي"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grains, seeds","tags":["collective","rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grain, cereal","tags":["collective","rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grains, kernels","tags":["collective","rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"granules","tags":["collective","rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pellets","tags":["collective","rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pills, pastilles","tags":["collective","rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"berries","tags":["collective","rare"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"acne, pustules, pimples","tags":["collective","rare"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ħab.ba/","/ħub.ba/","/ħubb/","/ħibb/","/ħabb/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6839","headword_ar":"حَبَّ","root":"Hb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, loved, beloved, an object of love, affected, liked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"approved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habuba","text_ar":"حَبُبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habiba","text_ar":"حَبِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~a A_ilaY~a h`*aA Al$~aYo'u","text_ar":"حَبَّ اـِلَىَّ هٰذَا الشَّىْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"text","text":",] inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~N","text_ar":"حُبٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This thing was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, an object of love to me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K. [The meaning is there indicated, but not expressed. In the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aY'a","text_ar":"الشَّىءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aYo'u","text_ar":"الشَّىْءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habubotu A_ilayohi","text_ar":"حَبُبْتُ اـِلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I became loved, beloved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an object of love, to him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[said to be] the only instance of its kind except"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$arurotu","text_ar":"شَرُرْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"labubotu","text_ar":"لَبُبْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA kunota HabiybFA walaqado Habibota","text_ar":"مَا كُنْتَ حَبِيبًا وَلَقَدْ حَبِبْتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou wast not loved, and thou hast become loved."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) See also 5. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~a","text_ar":"حَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", formed from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habuba","text_ar":"حَبُبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", by making the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"quiescent and incorporating it into the latter, is also a verb of praise [signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Beloved, lovely, pleasing, charming,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excellent, is"},{"kind":"text","text":"he, or it]; (TA;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~a","text_ar":"حُبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [which is more common,] formed from the same, by incorporating the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"into the latter after transferring the dammeh of the former to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"H","text_ar":"ح"},{"kind":"text","text":". (ISk, S, TA.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wazaAdahu kalafFA fiY AlHub~i A^ano manaEato\n                      \n                     \n                        waHab~a $ayoy^FA AlaY AlAnosaAni maA muniEaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And her denying increased his devotion in love: for lovely, as a thing, to man, is that which is denied"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And Sá'ideh says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"hajarato gaDuwbu waHab~a mano yatajan~abu\n                      \n                     \n                        waEadato EawaAdK duwna waloyika ta$oEibu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ghadoob hath forsaken"},{"kind":"text","text":"thee, ("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and lovely is the person who withdraweth far away,"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and obstacles in the way of thy drawing near have occurred to separate"},{"kind":"text","text":"thee and her]. (S, TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~a*aA","text_ar":"حَبَّذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.] ―         -b3-  [Both are also verbs of wonder.] You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~a bifulaAnK","text_ar":"حَبَّ بِفُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (As, S, and so in copies of the K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~a","text_ar":"حُبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (I 'Ak p. 236, [where both forms are mentioned as correct,] and so in the CK,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How beloved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lovely,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is such a one"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, K) to me! (As, S.) [See also 4.] A'Obeyd and Fr read this"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~a","text_ar":"حَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", saying that it means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habuba","text_ar":"حَبُبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bflAn","text_ar":"بفلان"},{"kind":"text","text":", and that the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"is rendered quiescent by the suppression of its dammeh, and incorporated into the latter. (S, * TA.)       -A2-  See also 4, in two places.       -A3-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~a","text_ar":"حَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [aor., accord. to analogy,"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He stood still, stopped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"paused."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)       -A4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hub~a","text_ar":"حُبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was fatigued,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tired."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["As","S","K"]}]}}